                <p class="listicle-lead">If you're a man over 40 watching your belly grow despite eating less and exercising more, I need you to understand something: <strong>it's not your fault.</strong></p>

                <p>After 20 years treating men with <strong>stubborn visceral fat</strong>, I've seen the same story hundreds of times. Intelligent, disciplined men doing everything "right" — <strong>cutting calories, hitting the gym, trying supplement after supplement</strong> — and watching the scale stay stuck or climb higher.</p>

                <p><strong>The problem isn't willpower.</strong> It isn't discipline. It isn't even your diet.</p>

                <p><strong>The problem is a biological mechanism that's literally turning your own testosterone against you.</strong></p>
