                <p>In medical school, we learned that testosterone naturally declines as men age — roughly <strong>1-2% per year after 30</strong>. This is normal. Expected. Nothing to worry about.</p>

                <p>What they didn't teach us — what most doctors still don't fully appreciate — is <strong>what happens when that declining testosterone meets accumulated belly fat.</strong></p>

                <p>It creates a <strong>feedback loop</strong>. A vicious cycle where your belly fat actively makes itself bigger, using your own hormones as fuel.</p>

