                <h2>Why Common Solutions Don't Work</h2>

                <p>Understanding this cycle explains why the most popular approaches fail for men over 40:</p>

                <p><strong>Calorie restriction.</strong> Eating less triggers your body's survival mechanisms. Your metabolism slows. Cortisol rises. And because you're in a stressed, calorie-deprived state, your body preferentially burns muscle for energy while <em>protecting</em> fat stores.</p>

