                <p>Once you've addressed conversion and started reducing visceral fat, you can support your body's own testosterone production. Adaptogens like <strong>Ashwagandha</strong> (specifically KSM-66) have robust evidence for <strong>increasing testosterone while reducing cortisol</strong>.</p>

                <div class="listicle-insight-box">
                    <p><strong>The crucial insight:</strong> These three pathways must be addressed simultaneously. Blocking conversion without targeting visceral fat leaves the fat in place. Boosting testosterone without blocking conversion feeds the problem. It's the combination that finally breaks the cycle.</p>
